<subSubSection id="1AF1EC8BBD4A77548303FD58FB641A3E" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5254BF00BD4A77548303FD58FB641A3E" blockId="3.[811,1457,594,2027]" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">
DIAGNOSIS. — This species differs from other 
<taxonomicName id="95EBC483BD4A775484DBFD58FA261BD7" box="[1269,1425,696,720]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="609F6312BD4A775484DBFD58FAFF1BD7" box="[1269,1352,696,720]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Solanum</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by subcapsular fruits that are entirely enclosed by calyx. It has supra axillary cyme inflorescence with 2-3 flowers. This species also has distinctive features such as obtuse leaf apex, unarmed petiole and pedicel, simple stigma and glabrous anther.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1AF1EC8BBD4A77548303FCB2FB1A1DDB" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="5254BF00BD4A77548303FCB2FB1A1DDB" blockId="3.[811,1457,594,2027]" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">
HABITAT AND PHENOLOGY. — 
<taxonomicName id="95EBC483BD4A77548465FCB2FAD51A6D" authority="Soosairaj" authorityName="Soosairaj &amp; Raja &amp; Balaguru &amp; Tagore" authorityYear="2021" box="[1099,1378,850,874]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulneyensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="609F6312BD4A77548465FCB2FAB31A6D" box="[1099,1284,850,874]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Solanum pulneyensis</emphasis>
Soosairaj
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="7BACDE69BD4A77548547FCB2FA071A6E" box="[1385,1456,850,873]" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was found growing in savanna forest in the Western Ghats of Palani Hills National Park, on a slope at 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4A775484B7FC67FB511A99" box="[1177,1254,903,927]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" unit="m" value="1300.0">1300 m</quantity>
elevation amidst tall grasses like 
<taxonomicName id="95EBC483BD4A7754838EFC41FAA51ABE" authority="(DC.) Stapf. The" authorityName="Stapf. The" baseAuthorityName="DC." box="[928,1298,929,953]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cymbopogon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="citratus">
<emphasis id="609F6312BD4A7754838EFC41FBD31ABE" box="[928,1124,929,953]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Cymbopogon citratus</emphasis>
(DC.) Stapf. The
</taxonomicName>
vegetation 
<typeStatus id="8D5001A2BD4A775485ABFC42FA181ABD" box="[1413,1455,930,954]" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">type</typeStatus>
has been described as sub-tropical hill savanna (8A/DS1) which is interrupted with patches of southern hill top wet evergreen forests (
<bibRefCitation id="367AC2F1BD4A7754831BFC11FB901D0F" author="CHAMPION H. G. &amp; SETH S. K." box="[821,1063,1008,1033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" pagination="256" refId="ref2558" refString="CHAMPION H. G. &amp; SETH S. K. 1968. - Revised Survey of the Forest Types of India. Manager of Publications, New Delhi: 255, 256." type="journal article" year="1968">Champion &amp; Seth 1968</bibRefCitation>
). The new species was found associated with 
<taxonomicName id="95EBC483BD4A77548375FBECFBCD1D24" authority="(Dennst.) Alston" authorityName="Alston" authorityYear="1929" baseAuthorityName="Dennst." box="[859,1146,1035,1059]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Phyllanthaceae" genus="Breynia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="retusa">
<emphasis id="609F6312BD4A77548375FBECFC6E1D24" box="[859,985,1036,1059]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Breynia retusa</emphasis>
(Dennst.) Alston
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="95EBC483BD4A775484AAFBECFA1D1D24" authority="(Jacq.) Kunth" authorityName="Kunth" baseAuthorityName="Jacq." box="[1156,1450,1035,1059]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Piperaceae" genus="Peperomia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Piperales" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="blanda">
<emphasis id="609F6312BD4A775484AAFBECFA921D24" box="[1156,1317,1035,1059]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Peperomia blanda</emphasis>
(Jacq.) Kunth
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="95EBC483BD4A77548305FBC5FBAC1D3A" authority="Cooke" authorityName="Cooke" box="[811,1051,1061,1085]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bhidei">
<emphasis id="609F6312BD4A77548305FBC5FC791D3A" box="[811,974,1061,1085]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="236">Kalanchoe bhidei</emphasis>
Cooke
