<subSubSection id="1AF1EC8BBD4C775280AAF993FAA61E2B" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" type="description">
<paragraph id="5254BF00BD4C775280AAF993FEA21F8C" blockId="5.[130,777,1651,2028]" box="[132,277,1651,1677]" pageId="5" pageNumber="238">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5254BF00BD4C775280AAF972FAA61E2B" blockId="5.[130,777,1651,2028]" lastBlockId="5.[811,1457,1491,1836]" pageId="5" pageNumber="238">
Armed, undershrub, 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C77528174F972FE081FAA" box="[346,447,1682,1709]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="cm" value="60.0" valueMax="70.0" valueMin="50.0">50-70 cm</quantity>
tall, stellate tomentose throughout. Stem stellate tomentose, prickled, prickles straight, 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C775280A8F932FF4D1FEB" box="[134,250,1746,1773]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1-1.5 mm</quantity>
, yellow. Leaves simple, alternate, oblong-ovate, 3-6.5 × 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C775280CEF912FE841E0B" box="[224,307,1778,1804]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="cm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2-4 cm</quantity>
, base truncate, oblique, margin undulate, stellate tomentose on both the surfaces, apex obtuse, midrib with 1 or 2 prickles below, lateral nerves 3-4 pairs, without prickles; petiole 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C77528115F8B2FE111E6B" box="[315,422,1874,1900]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.55" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="15.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="8.0">8-23 mm</quantity>
, prickled. Inflorescence a cyme, supra axillary, 2-3 flowered, peduncle 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C77528232F891FDC41E8B" box="[540,627,1905,1932]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5-6 mm</quantity>
long. Flowers 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C775280AAF871FF401EAB" box="[132,247,1937,1964]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="21.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="20.0">20-23 mm</quantity>
across, pedicel up to 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C775281F2F871FD9A1EAB" box="[476,557,1937,1964]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="18.0">18 mm</quantity>
, not prickled; Calyx cupular, rotate, 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C77528106F851FE3A1ECB" box="[296,397,1969,1996]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="9.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="9.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="9.0">9-10 mm</quantity>
, densely stellate tomentose without, glabrous within, lobes 5, lanceolate with prominent midnerves, 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C77528305FA33FC351CEA" box="[811,898,1491,1518]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5-6 mm</quantity>
, apex acuminate; Corolla rotate, 5 lobed, pale purple, lobes orbicular, 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C775283E3FA12FB931F0A" box="[973,1060,1522,1549]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4-5 mm</quantity>
, undulate, stellate tomentose without, glabrous inside, midnerve yellowish from the base; Stamens 5, filaments 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C7752839FF9D3FBBB1F4A" box="[945,1036,1587,1613]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1-2 mm</quantity>
, glabrous, anthers unequal, 3 long, 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C775285A4F9D3FCEC1F6A" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7-8 mm</quantity>
, falcate, 2 short, 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C77528436F9B2FBC21F6A" box="[1048,1141,1618,1645]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5-6 mm</quantity>
, lanceolate, glabrous, yellow, poricidal. Pistil 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C775283F9F992FB9E1F8A" box="[983,1065,1650,1677]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
; ovary ovoid, 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C77528491F992FA991F8A" box="[1215,1326,1650,1677]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1-1.5 mm</quantity>
, style 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C77528541F992FCEF1FAA" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="11.0">11-12 mm</quantity>
long, capillary, glabrous, curved; stigma simple. Fruit subcapsular, globose, 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C7752843BF952FBCD1FCA" box="[1045,1146,1714,1741]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8-10 mm</quantity>
across, pale green with white patches, fruiting calyx accrescent, 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C7752848BF932FAA81FEB" box="[1189,1311,1746,1772]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="13.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="13.0">13-14 mm</quantity>
, lobes 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C77528542F932FCEB1E0B" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="10.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="10.0">10-11 mm</quantity>
, stellately tomentose, not prickled. Seed rhomboid, 3.5× 
<quantity id="951312E5BD4C77528303F8F2FCC61E2B" box="[813,881,1810,1836]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
, pale brown, alveolate, margin bulged.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1AF1EC8BBD4C77518303F8B2FE7D1FEB" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="239" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5254BF00BD4C77528303F8B2FC281E6D" blockId="5.[813,1457,1874,2027]" box="[813,927,1874,1900]" pageId="5" pageNumber="238">AFFINITIES</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5254BF00BD4C77518303F891FE7D1FEB" blockId="5.[813,1457,1874,2027]" lastBlockId="6.[131,776,1491,1772]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="239" pageId="5" pageNumber="238">
<taxonomicName id="95EBC483BD4C77528303F891FBC51E8C" authority="Soosairaj" authorityName="Soosairaj &amp; Raja &amp; Balaguru &amp; Tagore" authorityYear="2021" box="[813,1138,1905,1931]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulneyensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="609F6312BD4C77528303F891FBB11E8C" box="[813,1030,1905,1931]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="238">Solanum pulneyensis</emphasis>
Soosairaj
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="7BACDE69BD4C775284AEF892FB621E8B" box="[1152,1237,1906,1932]" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is a distinct species since it has a subcapsular fruit. It resembles with 
<taxonomicName id="95EBC483BD4C77528564F872FCD51ECB" authority="Nees" authorityName="Nees" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="5" pageNumber="238" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wightii">
<emphasis id="609F6312BD4C77528564F872FA061EAC" box="[1354,1457,1937,1964]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="238">S. wightii</emphasis>
Nees
</taxonomicName>
in having accrescent fruit calyx that covers the fruit completely but differs in having subcapsular fruit, obtuse leaf apex, glabrous anther, calyx and petiole without prickles (
<tableCitation id="1F698ABBBD4F775180A0FA13FF691F0A" box="[142,222,1523,1549]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="3.[132,143,219,236]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="TABLE 1. — Features that distinguish S. pulneyensis Soosairaj, sp. nov. from S. wightii Nees." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0694EF88BD4A775480AAFF3BFEB01804" pageId="6" pageNumber="239" tableUuid="0694EF88BD4A775480AAFF3BFEB01804">Table 1</tableCitation>
). It is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="95EBC483BD4F775181E4FA13FDFE1F0A" box="[458,585,1523,1549]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="6" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cordatum">
<emphasis id="609F6312BD4F775181E4FA13FDFE1F0A" box="[458,585,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">S. cordatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having similar features like oblong-ovate leaves, 2-3 flowered cymes but differs in having subcapsular fruit that dehisces irregularly at apex and fruit that is pale green with white patches. Although most of the 
<taxonomicName id="95EBC483BD4F77518170F992FDBD1F8B" box="[350,522,1650,1676]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="6" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="609F6312BD4F77518170F992FE0D1F8B" box="[350,442,1650,1676]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">Solanum</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
have berry as common fruit 
<typeStatus id="8D5001A2BD4F77518092F973FF5A1FAA" box="[188,237,1683,1709]" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">type</typeStatus>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="367AC2F1BD4F775180D6F972FE3B1FAB" author="SYMON D. E." box="[248,396,1682,1708]" pageId="6" pageNumber="239" pagination="321 - 331" refId="ref3012" refString="SYMON D. E. 1979. - Fruit diversity and dispersal in Solanum in Australia. Journal of the Adelaide Botanic Gardens 1: 321 - 331." type="journal article" year="1979">Symon (1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="367AC2F1BD4F775181B5F972FE641FAB" author="SYMON D. E." box="[411,467,1682,1708]" pageId="6" pageNumber="239" pagination="1 - 367" refId="ref3041" refString="SYMON D. E. 1981. - A revision of the genus Solanum in Australia. Journal of the Adelaide Botanic Gardens 4: 1 - 367." type="journal article" year="1981">1981</bibRefCitation>
) reports subcapsular fruit in 
<taxonomicName id="95EBC483BD4F775180ABF952FE2E1FCB" authority="Dunal" authorityName="Dunal" box="[133,409,1714,1740]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="6" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rostratum">
<emphasis id="609F6312BD4F775180ABF952FEFD1FCB" box="[133,330,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">Solanum rostratum</emphasis>
Dunal
</taxonomicName>
, a widespread weed in his revision of Australian 
<taxonomicName id="95EBC483BD4F77518138F932FE7D1FEB" box="[278,458,1746,1772]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="6" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="609F6312BD4F77518138F932FEC51FEB" box="[278,370,1746,1772]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">Solanum</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
